  "detailed_description": "<span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1392000/extras/5805d39e0045bf977c5d19dbd8500baf.poster.avif?t=1604582130\" width=600 height=338 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1392000/extras/5805d39e0045bf977c5d19dbd8500baf.webm?t=1604582130\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1392000/extras/5805d39e0045bf977c5d19dbd8500baf.mp4?t=1604582130\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span><br>Each episode will have 60 cycles. These act as turns for the player. For each turn, a card is generated, along with a line of text and two options. The two options you receive influence a number of resources your station is managing. The goal is to not have too little or too much of a resource. In other words, you want to have a balance of all of them. As you progress, more resources become available to you. Also, as you play, you have the opportunity to collect items, which will trigger small scenarios that add variation to the game.",
  "about_the_game": "<span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1392000/extras/5805d39e0045bf977c5d19dbd8500baf.poster.avif?t=1604582130\" width=600 height=338 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1392000/extras/5805d39e0045bf977c5d19dbd8500baf.webm?t=1604582130\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1392000/extras/5805d39e0045bf977c5d19dbd8500baf.mp4?t=1604582130\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span><br>Each episode will have 60 cycles. These act as turns for the player. For each turn, a card is generated, along with a line of text and two options. The two options you receive influence a number of resources your station is managing. The goal is to not have too little or too much of a resource. In other words, you want to have a balance of all of them. As you progress, more resources become available to you. Also, as you play, you have the opportunity to collect items, which will trigger small scenarios that add variation to the game.",
